          "text": "<teammate-message teammate_id=\"carddav-reviewer\" color=\"green\" summary=\"CardDAV test quality review complete\">\n## Task #2: CardDAV Test Quality & RFC Compliance Review\n\nI reviewed all three test files against their source files and the RFC 6352 specification. Here are my findings organized by test file.\n\n---\n\n### 1. ecard-carddav-test.el (~2500 lines, ~80+ tests)\n\n**GOOD: Authentication coverage is thorough**\n- Tests basic auth, bearer token, OAuth2 creation, header generation, expiration, refresh, and validation edge cases (lines 87-981)\n- Properly tests auth-source integration with mock (lines 985-1020)\n- Tests auth function resolution in server creation (lines 1038-1053, 1774-1791)\n\n**GOOD: Core protocol operations are well-tested**\n- Discovery chain (principal → addressbook-home → addressbooks) is tested individually and end-to-end (lines 149-192, 621-681)\n- PUT/GET/DELETE with ETag validation covers happy path and conflicts (lines 194-343)\n- Multiget batch retrieval tested with multiple resources, empty list, absolute URLs, parse errors (lines 1179-1942)\n- Retry logic for 5xx with exponential backoff tested (lines 1843-1875)\n\n**GOOD: RFC 6352 compliance areas tested**\n- sync-collection REPORT body generation and handling (lines 1493-1504, 2055-2127)\n- addressbook-multiget REPORT body (lines 1078-1087, 1508-1516)\n- PROPFIND body generation with proper namespaces (lines 1067-1076)\n- ETag-based concurrency control (lines 256-313)\n- Sync-token incremental sync (lines 406-443, 2055-2093)\n- CTag-based change detection (lines 1558-1587, 1946-2013)\n\n**GOOD: Mock server internals are independently validated**\n- XML parsing, escaping, response construction, PROPFIND at various depths (lines 1097-1175, 2129-2268)\n- Edge cases: invalid vCard PUT, missing addressbook paths, nonexistent resource PROPFIND (lines 2161-2214)\n\n**GOOD: URL resolution tested**\n- Absolute URL, absolute path, and relative path resolution (lines 1627-1646)\n- Principal and addressbook-home URL extraction with both relative and absolute hrefs (lines 2311-2393)\n\n**GOOD: vCard 3.0 compatibility and line-ending handling**\n- Tests version 3.0 serialization path and LF line ending conversion (lines 1722-1770)\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Conflict resolution tests create sync objects without addressbook**\n- Lines 1229-1379: Tests like `ecard-carddav-test-sync-conflict-server-wins` create `ecard-carddav-sync` directly without `ecard-carddav-sync-create`, bypassing validation. This works because the conflict resolution function only reads the `:strategy` slot, but it's fragile if the constructor ever adds validation logic.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Some tests don't verify complete state**\n- `ecard-carddav-test-sync-collection-deleted-resources` (line 2097): Only checks `(listp result)` after deletion but doesn't verify the deleted path appears in `:deleted` or that the local cache was cleaned. The test exercises the code path but doesn't fully assert correct behavior.\n\n**ISSUE (minor): Mock state leakage potential**\n- The `ecard-carddav-test--mock-server` and `ecard-carddav-test--temp-dir` module-level variables could leak between tests if `unwind-protect` teardown is missed. All tests do use unwind-protect properly, but a single missed teardown could cascade failures.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Add test for .well-known/carddav redirect**\n- RFC 6352 Section 11 specifies service discovery via `.well-known/carddav`. The mock server doesn't appear to test this redirect path, which is important for real-world compatibility.\n\n**SUGGESTION: Test Content-Type header in PUT requests**\n- RFC 6352 requires `text/vcard` content type. The tests verify data correctness but don't explicitly assert the Content-Type header sent in PUT requests.\n\n---\n\n### 2. ecard-carddav-map-test.el (~1530 lines, ~45+ tests)\n\n**GOOD: Comprehensive functional coverage**\n- Empty addressbook, no-modifications, all-modifications, partial-modifications, sk