e)\n- `ecard-display-test-contacts-populate-fallback` swallows all errors making it imprecise\n- No test for multiple address extraction roundtrip in widget tests\n- No test for user declining discard in `ecard-display-contact-quit`\n\n### Strengths\n- Excellent mock server integration tests with proper setup/teardown\n- Thorough error path coverage (parse, validation, generic, conflict errors)\n- Good use of `cl-letf` for mocking interactive functions\n- Strong helper function unit tests with edge cases\n- Full roundtrip and data integrity tests\n- Proper `unwind-protect` cleanup in nearly all tests\n\n### Summary Table\n| Category | display-test | widget-test |\n|----------|-------------|-------------|\n| Critical | 1 | 1 (shared: silent `when` guards) |\n| Moderate | 3 | 2 |\n| Minor | 3 | 3 |\n\nThe highest-priority fix is replacing `when` guards with `should` assertions across both files. This would prevent tests from silently passing when widget lookup fails.\n</teammate-message>",
